The challenge of AI has long been to create a system that can truly understand, reason, and learn from human language—but we’re well on our way to finding solutions. Here, SVP and Director of IBM Research Dario Gil shares a glimpse into what’s next for AI and natural language processing.👇

🔵  IBM is teaching AI the languages of code and chemistry.

🔵  We’re pioneering new ways to modernize applications with AI.

🔵  We’ve launched Project CodeNet, offering 14,000,000 samples of code as part of an open source data set.

🔵  IBM Research is accelerating the discovery of new materials for a fraction of the time and financial resources than traditionally needed.
